Veritas Asset Management Appoints Ian Barnes as Chief Executive, Effective Early 2017
Sep 28 16
Veritas Asset Management announced that Ian Barnes, former head of UBS Asset Management for Ireland and the UK, has been appointed to the newly created position of chief executive. He will join in early 2017, becoming part of the managing partners board. Barnes had been head of asset management at UBS for UK and Ireland since 2012. Before that, he was at Russell Investments, where his initial role as senior investment consultant evolved into a focus on fiduciary management.


