About - VeritasVeritasMenuarrowLog inBy logging in you are agreeing to our Terms of useForgot your password?Veritas Asset Management has the key investment objective of delivering long term real returns to its clients. Our aim is to both protect and grow the purchasing power of our clients’ capital over time.Our PartnershipEstablished in 2003, the company is run with a partnership structure and culture. We have offices in London and Hong Kong.Veritas Asset Management is led by five Managing Partners: Charles Richardson (Fund Manager and Chairman), Andy Headley (Fund Manager and Head of Global), Ezra Sun (Fund Manager and Head of Asia), Ian Barnes (Chief Executive Officer) and Richard Grant (Chief Operating Officer).Meet our teamWe offer both Global and Asian equity strategies which have distinct investment teams dedicated to the products offered within those strategies.GlobalAsiaexpandOur PhilosophySince our foundation in 2003 the Veritas philosophy has been built upon two founding principles of Real Returns and Partnership.Real ReturnsWe manage money on behalf of clients following our Veritas Real Return Approach, implemented by an investment team with substantial experience and a proven long term track record. The approach demands that all potential investments are analysed from an absolute basis rather than relative to any benchmark or index. The focus is on protecting and growing client’s capital in real terms with exceeding an equity benchmark a fall out of that process.PartnershipOur business is run with a partnership structure and culture. We align our interests as owners in partnership with our clients. Our partners and employees are invested alongside our clients on the same terms. We are an investment-led organisation that controls the growth of our business. It’s important to us that clients fully understand our approach and share a similar objective or mind-set.expandOur Key PrinciplesThe key principles of the firm can be summarised as:1Focused on protecting and growing the real value of clients’ capital.2Partnership structure and culture.3Alignment of interests with clients through controlled growth, co-investment and investment objectives.4Investment-led culture and independence. The context investors work within is critical.5Broad spread of clients with a focus on our core capabilities.6Genuine long term perspective. Investments made with a 5 year plus time frame.7Integrity. We avoid herd-like mentality and we are not ‘all things to all people’ whether in investment or in appealing to clients.CloseVeritas Asset Management has the key investment objective of delivering long term real returns to its clients. Our aim is to both protect and grow the purchasing power of our clients’ capital over time.Our website is designed to run on modern, compatible web-browsers with Javascript enabled. It looks like your browser is not compatible with our full website. You can find a list of compatible browsers here.Veritas Asset Management LLP 
90 Long Acre, London WC2E 9RAT +44 (0) 20 3758 9900F +44 (0) 20 3070 0990investorservices@veritas-asset.comAsia - VeritasVeritasMenuarrowLog inBy logging in you are agreeing to our Terms of useForgot your password?The Veritas Asian strategies are focused on protecting and growing the real value of clients’ capital over our rolling 5 year investment horizon or a full economic cycle.Asian OverviewThe investment process starts with a top down approach focused on identifying trends and themes as well as other macro-economic factors which offer characteristics to look for in companies. This is followed by fundamental stock analysis to identify the likely beneficiaries and then strict valuation discipline to pay the right price.
Given the nature of the Asian markets the strategies not only invest in ‘core’ companies that deliver sustainable growth in excess of the market and that typically deliver above average yield, they also invest in cyclical and special situations positions that are benefiting from shorter term price catalysts. These may be short positions as well as long, depending on the strategy.The Veritas Asian Fund is long only with an objective relative to an index. The Veritas China Fund and Real Return Asian Fund are long/short strategies where the objectives are absolute in nature.expandAsian StrategiesVeritas Asian Characteristics– Pan Asian long only strategy investing in equities in Asia Pacific ex Japan.
– Objective is to achieve long term growth of capital over and above the MSCI AC Asia-Pacific ex Japan, with lower than market volatility.
– Focus on quality companies that benefit from long term structural growth as well as opportunities in quality cyclical winners and special situations.
– Positions will be mostly in large cap companies.
– Available as a segregated portfolio.
– Available as a Fund (Veritas Asian Fund).expandVeritas China Characteristics– Long/short fund investing in equities in Chinese corporates or China related corporates irrespective of their countries of listing.
– Objective is to achieve long term capital growth with low volatility. Aims to achieve real returns irrespective of market conditions rather than reference to an index. 
– Focus on quality companies that benefit from long term structural growth as well as opportunities in quality cyclical winners and special situations.
– Positions will be mostly in large cap companies.
– Available as a Fund (Veritas China Fund).expandReal Return Asian Characteristics– Monthly dealing long/short Pan Asian fund investing in equities in the Asia Pacific region.
– The Fund's objective is to achieve long term capital growth. More specifically, the Fund’s target is to achieve an absolute return on a compound annualised basis of 10%.
– Focus on quality companies that benefit from long term structural growth as well as opportunities in quality cyclical winners and special situations.
– Positions will be mostly in large cap companies.
– Available as a QIAIF managed in accordance with AIFMD (The Real Return Asian Fund).expandCloseVeritas Asset Management has the key investment objective of delivering long term real returns to its clients. Our aim is to both protect and grow the purchasing power of our clients’ capital over time.Our website is designed to run on modern, compatible web-browsers with Javascript enabled. It looks like your browser is not compatible with our full website. You can find a list of compatible browsers here.Veritas Asset Management LLP 
